      <h2 id="identity">Identity / participants</h2>

      <p>
        Participants in the PDTF ecosystem use <strong>W3C DIDs</strong>:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li><code>did:key:...</code> — used for examples in the trust-framework repo</li>
        <li><code>did:jwk:...</code> — JSON Web Key DID method</li>
        <li><code>did:web:...</code> — domain-anchored DIDs (likely for OPDA-accredited members)</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        Example participants in the public test infrastructure are at
        <code>source/07-website/source/public/trustframework/api/members/did:*</code>.
      </p>

      <h2 id="externalStandards">External standards alignment</h2>

      <div class="card-grid">
        <div class="card">
          <div class="pill pill--info">W3C</div>
          <h3>Verifiable Credentials Data Model 1.1 + 2.0</h3>
          <p>The provenance/verification foundation. Locally archived for offline reference.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <div class="pill pill--info">W3C</div>
          <h3>Decentralized Identifiers 1.0</h3>
          <p>How participants are identified. Archived as <code>did-core.html</code>.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <div class="pill pill--info">UK Gov</div>
          <h3>DIATF</h3>
          <p>Digital Identity and Attributes Trust Framework. Strategic alignment partner.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <div class="pill pill--info">Linux Foundation</div>
          <h3>Trust Over IP (ToIP)</h3>
          <p>The 4-layer governance model PDTF follows. See <a href="07-toip-governance.html">ToIP governance</a>.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

